  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p>\r\n<p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p>\r\n<p>Grate the <strong>Italian hard&nbsp;</strong><strong>cheese</strong></p>\r\n<p>Chop the<strong> chives</strong> finely</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/507._step-1-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/507._step-1-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/507._step-1-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/507._step-1-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/507._step-1-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> linguine</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a large pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p>\r\n<p>Cook the<strong> linguine</strong> for 8-10 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p>\r\n<p>Once done, drain the <strong>linguine</strong>, reserving 300ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]</span> of the <strong>starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/507._step-1-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/507._step-1-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/507._step-1-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/507._step-1-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/507._step-1-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong> over a medium-high heat&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the<strong> pancetta&nbsp;lardons</strong> and cook for 3 min or until they're starting to crisp</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/507._step-1-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/507._step-1-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/507._step-1-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/507._step-1-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/507._step-1-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><span class=\"text-highlight\">Meanwhile, wash, dry and rip the<strong> red gem lettuce</strong> into rough, bite-size pieces</span></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"text-highlight\">Combine the <strong>white wine vinegar</strong> with 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> - this is your <strong>dressing&nbsp;</strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"text-highlight\">Once the<strong> pancetta </strong>is crispy, reduce the heat to low and add the<strong> chopped garlic&nbsp;</strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"text-highlight\">Cook for a further 1 min, stirring constantly, then remove from the heat&nbsp;</span></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/507._step-1-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/507._step-1-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/507._step-1-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/507._step-1-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/507._step-1-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><span class=\"text-highlight\">Crack the <strong>eggs</strong> into a mixing bowl</span></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"text-highlight\">Add the <strong>grated cheese</strong>, <strong>clotted cream</strong>, half of the <strong>chopped chives</strong> (save the rest for garnish) and season generously with both <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"text-highlight\">Whisk with a fork as if you were making scrambled eggs- this is your <strong>egg mixture</strong></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/507._step-1-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/507._step-1-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/507._step-1-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/507._step-1-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/507._step-1-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>drained linguine</strong> to the pancetta pan with a few splashes of the <strong>starchy cooking water</strong> and return the pan to a medium-high heat</p>\r\n<p>Cook for a further 2 min or until most of the water has evaporated, stirring often</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/507._step-1-6-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/507._step-1-6-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/507._step-1-6-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/507._step-1-6-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/507._step-1-6-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Reduce the heat to very low, add the <strong>egg mixture</strong> and stir continuously for 30 sec-1 min or until the mixture has thickened ever so slightly, adding more <strong>cooking water</strong> if you need to loosen it a bit - this is your <strong>carbonara</strong></p>\r\n<p>Tip: make sure your heat is very low, otherwise you will make scrambled eggs rather than a smooth sauce!</p>\r\n<p>Dress the <strong>red gem</strong> with your dressing</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/507._step-1-7-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/507._step-1-7-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
